verses.roman:
tulasī namaskari' haridāsera dvāre yāñā
gosāñire namaskari' rahilā dāṇḍāñā

synonyms: tulasī namaskari'-after offering obeisances to the tulasī plant; haridāsera—of Ṭhākura Haridāsa; dvāre—at the door; yāñā—going; gosāñire—unto the ācārya; namaskari'-offering obeisances; rahilā dāṇḍāñā—remained standing.
translation: After offering obeisances to the tulasī plant, she went to the door of Haridāsa Ṭhākura, offered him obeisances and stood there.
